# sfShortcutKeyPlugin

## Install

Configure your filters.yml adding :

    [yml]
    shortcuts:
      class: sfShortcutKeyFilter


## Configure 

To configure your shorcuts set the config files shortcuts.yml in yout directories

The structure is the next one :

    [yml]
    all:
      shortcuts:
        keys: # Part for direct key code Only one key pressed
          a: #The name of the code
            url: @route # or module/index to redirect on the key pressed
        alt: # Part for ALT+ <smth>
        ctrl: #same for CTRL+<smth>
        shift: # SHIFT+<smth>
        

